    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-11T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="281"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d281">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/980a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-11T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 11, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. The following is for the consideration of the Minister. It is the desire of
                    the Department that you familiarize yourself as soon as possible with the
                    Bolivia–Paraguay situation in the Chaco. Please report action taken on telegrams
                    No. 1, January 6, 5 p.m.,<note n="34" xml:id="d281fn34">See telegram No. 5,
                        January 6, 5 p.m., to the Chargé in Uruguay, <ref target="#pg_311">p.
                            311</ref>.</note> No. 4, January 27, 6 p.m.,<note n="35"
                        xml:id="d281fn35">Not printed.</note> and No. 5, January 30, 6 p.m., and
                    whether in your opinion there is a likelihood that Paraguay will now accept the
                    Uruguayan suggestion. While this suggestion of Uruguay to carry out the
                    conciliation agreement of September 12, 1929 is not accepted by Paraguay,
                    Bolivia advances that as a reason for not considering the note sent by the
                    neutral Governments to Bolivia on January 9<note n="36" xml:id="d281fn36">See
                        telegram No. 2, January 6, 5 p.m., to the Chargé in Bolivia, <ref
                            target="#pg_327">p. 327</ref>.</note> with a view to bringing about a
                    settlement of the basic question in dispute. It had been the hope of the
                    Department that the Government of Paraguay would not feel that its objection to
                    the Uruguayan proposal was of sufficient importance to allow it possibly to
                    jeopardize a settlement of the Chaco question.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
